<dl id="s17018e"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="us17" href="#s17018e">Ithaca: </a><a href="../../ff/unbs/s17all.htm#s17018e">sector 18(e)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> plumbline</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><b>Direction of Gravity</b>. The direction of the force of gravity at any place is called the <i>vertical</i> direction; it is indicated to the eye by a <mark><i>plumb line</i></mark>, that is, a string supporting a small weight in a state of rest. <small> Wentworth and Hill, <a name="TBOP" href="/udra/udex.htm#tbop"><cite title="source">A Text-Book of Physics</cite></a> (1904), 43</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
